## Visual Ratio

| Color family | Target use |
| --- | ---: |
| Black navy and federal navy | 72% |
| White and cool gray text | 18% |
| Federal blue accents | 7% |
| Gold premium accents | 2% |
| Cyan and status colors | 1% |

## Usage Rules

- Federal blue owns the store identity: navigation, primary action system, active states, and structural accents.
- Gold is a premium signal: lifetime access, featured value, investor cues, and small separators. Do not use gold for entire cards or large text blocks.
- Cyan is reserved for data, terminal details, charts, and small technical marks. It should not dominate borders, shadows, or page backgrounds.
- Page backgrounds stay quiet: black navy to federal navy, with no bright glows and no tiled page texture.
- Borders are mostly blue-gray and low contrast. Use strong borders only for active controls or purchase states.
- Primary buttons use action blue with white text. They should feel official and dependable, not neon.
- Product cues:
  - Imperium Option Trading Terminal: white, federal blue, small technical cyan.
  - Imperium Investor: black navy, white, restrained gold.

## Component Guidance

### Page Background

Use a non-repeating background for the full app. It should feel like an official site shell, not a trading terminal grid.

```css
html {
  background: #05080F;
}

body {
  background:
    radial-gradient(900px 360px at 50% -180px, rgba(47, 111, 166, 0.26), transparent 68%),
    linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(11, 22, 38, 0.98) 0%, rgba(5, 8, 15, 0.98) 34rem, #05080F 100%),
    #05080F;
  background-attachment: fixed;
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
  background-size: 100% 100%, 100% 100%;
}
```

Avoid full-page grid textures, repeated dot patterns, and obvious image tiles. If a product-specific data grid is needed, keep it inside a contained product preview only.

